cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.PL 

The paper discusses a technique for optimizing stochastic computing, which is a topic related to electronic design automation (EDA) and computer architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), which covers research on new and innovative technologies in computer science. The paper also involves the use of mixed integer programming, which falls under the category of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of arithmetic operations, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes a synthesis formulation, which is related to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
